"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Freebody","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English  <i>fre</i> ‘free’ +  <i>bodi</i> ‘body, physique; person, individual’ (Old English  <i>frēo</i>,  <i>frīo</i> +  <i>bodig</i>), used of a ‘free man’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Freebody was born on 24 September 1433, in Stepney, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Freebody, was 28 and his mother, Anne Matilda Benton, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Nightingale. He died on 30 August 1491, in Castlemaine, Victoria, Australia, at the age of 57."},"et":{"24 September 1433–30 August 1491":"24. september 1433–30. august 1491","1433–1491":"1433–1491","1433–Female":"1433–Surnud","1460–1484":"1460–1484","1404–1437":"1404–1437","1407–1485":"1407–1485","24 September 1433":"24. september 1433","1484":"1484","1460":"1460","23 Sep 1485":"23. september 1485","1491":"1491","1437":"1437","1404":"1404","1433":"1433","30 August 1491":"30. august 1491","1430":"1430","1485":"1485","1407":"1407","06 Nov 1437":"6. november 1437","Islington, London, England":"Islington, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stepney, Middlesex, England":"Stepney, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa,